description:
We are looking for a Project Art Director to join the team here at Starbreeze Entertainment to refine and lead the artistic vision of PAYDAY 3 Live. This role will require you to inspire others, both as a leader and as an artist. You will report to our Studio Art Director.




 As a key production member, you’ll serve as a motivational catalyst and conduit of communication for all departments. As an artist and visionary, your concepts, guidance and support will define the look and ensure that all teams are creating a cohesive game experience.




 You should have experience developing AA+ games in an Art Director role. With a deep understanding of art pipelines and look development, you will be adept at facilitating cross-team development and collaboration.




 Our team is ripe with opportunities to take on and this candidate must possess a desire to embrace new challenges and nurture a fun and inspiring environment!




 This role has a requirement of 3 days per week onsite in Stockholm.




**Responsibilities:**
* Continue to develop the creative vision, including style, tone and visual language across all facets of PAYDAY 3 Live;
* Create concepts and other benchmark assets that inspire, and set the bar for production;
* Use your knowledge and experience of character and environment design to enable the team to create high quality art by coaching, mentoring and teaching through doing;
* Use your leadership skills and experience to lead the art team, and mentor and develop staff of all levels;
* Collaborate with functional Leads to facilitate and manage alignment between our departments and project needs;
* Compile or produce reference material which shapes the visual narrative and guides content teams in it’s execution;
* Make presentations regarding art direction, process, goals and results;
* Organize with other craft Leads and Directors reviewing and validating in-game assets to guarantee consistency and quality;
* Manage overall progress of our project’s development, assuring that all disciplines support each other.


**Requirements:**
* Proven experience working as an Art Director on AA+ games and/or live service;
* A strong art portfolio, with proven experience in character and environment design;
* Knowledge of 3D modeling and sculpting pipelines, with a willingness to teach through doing;
* Proven capacity to visualize and evolve existing brands, and successfully delivering them from concept to execution;
* Strong inter-departmental communication skills with a deep understanding of how all disciplines collaborate on a production pipeline (narrative, programming, design, animation, etc);
* Broad-mindedness, you’re open to new ideas following established art direction;
* Excellent written, verbal and visual communication skills in English;
* An experienced people leader and follower, who understands the competencies of your team, what they and you need to excel, and how to inspire great performance.


**Still reading? Good, because here’s the best part:**
 We offer you a position at a company where we value empowerment, agility and ownership. While we evolve we want you to grow with us and to develop as a professional.




**What more do we offer?**
* Competitive salaries with annual reviews
* Private medical insurance
* Annual wellness benefit
* Referral bonuses
* Long term incentive bonus scheme
* Pension on top of salary (≈50% above collective agreement standard for Sweden employees)
* Relocation support if you move from abroad to Stockholm
* Ideal office location in central Stockholm
* Massage sessions once a month in the Stockholm office


 Sounds good? Then we can’t wait to see your CV and look forward to meeting you. We recommend that you apply as soon as possible as selection and interviews are held continuously. Please submit your CV and cover letter in English.




*Starbreeze values diversity and inclusion, and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We welcome you as who you are, no matter where you are from or what games you play. If there are preparations or accommodations that we can make to help ensure that you have a comfortable and positive interview experience, please let us know.*
*Recruitment agencies may not submit CVs through this website or directly to hiring managers. Starbreeze Entertainment does not accept unsolicited recruitment agency CVs, and will not pay fees to any third-party agency or company that does not have a signed agreement with us.*

We have been dedicated to the power tool industry for 30 years, with over 5,000 employees globally and products sold and distributed in more than 60 countries worldwide.

Mechanical Engineer-Torque Wrenches  
Job Description:  
1. Identify user pain points, gain insight into market demand, establish forward-looking product development strategies, and form the development plan for fixed-twist series products;  
2. Participate in product concept discussions, contribute personal understanding of the product, and cooperate with the marketing department to complete the product definition;  
3. Undertake the content of product definition and transform it into technical language, and collaborate with the R&D team of electronic control and motor to form the product development path;  
4. Review the overall product design scheme, component structure design;  
5. Work with mould inspection, parts process validation and supplier selection;  
6. Participate in the definition of product quality and the development of inspection specifications for fixed-twist products;  
7. Develop the overall development capability of the team;

Job Requirements:  
1. Bachelor degree or above, majoring in mechanical design or mechatronics;  
2. Good communication skills, Chinese is a plus, familiar with at least one commonly used 3D software;  
3. More than 8 years of experience in product development or design of mechanical clutch-type and sensor-type torque setting tools;  
4. Analyse the advantages and shortcomings of the current benchmark clutch-type and sensor-type products, and form an optimised technical solution;  
5. Analyse and sort out the product development planning and technical modules of clutch-type and sensor-type tools, integrate R&D resources, and sequentially overcome each technical module;  
6. Complete the mechanical clutch type, sensor-type torsion tool system technology definition as well as design;  
7. Familiar with the technical parameters and selection requirements of the core technical modules of torque setting tools;  
8. Familiar with the definition and implementation principle of the tightening strategy, docking collaborative departments to complete the function implementation;

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: 40 000,00kr - 90 000,00kr per month

Experience:

* mechanical clutch-type and sensor-type torque setting tools: 8 years (Required)

Language:

* English (Required)
* Chinese (Preferred)

Work Location: Remote
